<!-- Tutorial steps -->
<div class="container">

  <p class="mt-3">Now that you have installed <a href="https://java.com" target="_blank">Java</a> and <a href="https://maven.apache.org" target="_blank">Apache Maven</a>, let's create a starter <a href="https://maven.apache.org" target="_blank">Maven</a> project and add a reference to the <a href="http://salesforce-marketingcloud.github.io/FuelSDK-Java/" target="_blank">Marketing Cloud Java SDK</a>.</p>

  <!-- Step 1 -->
  <div class="card mt-3">
    <div class="card-block">
      <div class="card-header text-white" style="background-color: #00AA9E;">Step 2.1: Create a new Java project using Maven</div>
      <div class="card-body">
        <p class="card-text">Run the commands below in a Terminal window to create an empty Java project using Maven.
          This will create the directory <code>sfmc-java-sample</code> with a basic Maven project and <code>pom.xml</code> file. If you prefer, you can perform this step using an IDE such as NetBeans or Eclipse.
        </p>
        <pre class="command-line" style="max-height: 30em" data-user="user" data-host="MacBook" data-src="/code-snippets/java/mvn-newproject.sh"></pre>
        <p class="card-text"><span class="fa fa-star text-success"></span>&nbsp;You have sucessfully created a new empty Maven project for your Java app.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Step 2 -->
  <div class="card mt-3">
    <div class="card-block">
      <div class="card-header text-white" style="background-color: #00AA9E;">Step 2.2: Add a reference to the Marketing Cloud Java SDK</div>
      <div class="card-body">

          <p class="card-text">Change directories into your newly created project.</p>
          <pre class="command-line" style="max-height: 30em" data-user="user" data-host="MacBook" data-src="/code-snippets/java/cd-sample-dir.sh"></pre>
  
          <p class="card-text">You should have a file called <code>pom.xml</code> in your Maven project located in the directory <code>~/sfmc-java-sample</code>. Open <code>pom.xml</code> in your favorite text editor and replace its contents with the XML below. Save and close the file.</p>
          <p class="card-text">Lines <code>20-25</code> add a reference to the <a href="http://salesforce-marketingcloud.github.io/FuelSDK-Java/" target="_blank">Marketing Cloud Java SDK</a> to your Maven project.
            With this change, Maven automatically downloads and uses the <a href="http://salesforce-marketingcloud.github.io/FuelSDK-Java/" target="_blank">Marketing Cloud Java SDK</a> from the 
            <a href="https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/com.github.salesforce-marketingcloud/fuelsdk" target="_blank">Maven Central repository</a> when you build your project.</p>

          <pre class="line-numbers" data-line="20-25" data-src="/code-snippets/java/mvn-pom.xml"></pre>

          <p class="card-text"><span class="fa fa-star text-success"></span>&nbsp;You have sucessfully created a starter Maven project and added a reference to the <a href="http://salesforce-marketingcloud.github.io/FuelSDK-Java/" target="_blank">Marketing Cloud Java SDK.</a> Maven will automatically resolve, download, and install all dependencies for you when you build the project.</p>
          <p class="card-text"><span class="fa fa-thumbs-o-up text-success"></span>&nbsp;You're ready to write some Java code that uses Marketing Cloud!</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

